body_content.explanation: to wrongly say that something has a particular date or age, or that something happened or was made at a particular time:
examples: Most of the manuscripts were misdated by ten to twenty years.
In 1911 he designed a building which everyone today would mis-date as 1930 or 1935.

body_content.explanation: to write the wrong date on something:
examples: Claims were electronically misdated so that it would seem they had been processed on time.
The customer complained about the misdated baby blanket.
